Class CurrentDinersRow

java.lang.Object
Client.CurrentDinersRow
public class CurrentDinersRow extends Object
Represents a single row in the "Current Diners" table.

This class is used as a JavaFX model object and exposes its fields as observable properties to allow binding with TableView.

  • Constructor Details

    • CurrentDinersRow

      public CurrentDinersRow(int tableNumber, String customerName, int peopleCount, String checkInTime, String status)
      Creates a new row representing diners currently seated in the restaurant.
      Parameters:
      tableNumber - table number assigned to the diners
      customerName - name of the customer
      peopleCount - number of people at the table
      checkInTime - check-in time as a formatted string
      status - current dining status
